Incident Description: [MOBI]Caída ratio de avance de “Pago” a “Confirmación” 19/02/2018
Resolution Description: [2018/02/26] LEDA.lnavio: reasignamos incidencia planteando la siguiente duda: Con esto que indicas “There are already payment failure alerts in the system that runs on standard cases and based on them we can check whether the problem is at specific server and related to specific type of payment and specific country” à quieres decir que cuando vuelva a ocurrir en el futuro, ¿con estas alertas se podrá detectar el problema en “tiempo real” y no al día siguiente cuando se saquen las gráficas? [2018/02/23]NIIT.vkumar: On the booking flow when customer reaches at prepayment authorization page then system stores the data of some of payment type selected in IBP_TARJETA_CREDITO_EXTERNAL_KEY and its sub parameters. This data relates to user selected options and served withcached xml This is not fixed as the data depends on user opted option and their combinations to populate the value. So parameters can be different based on flow. So it can be or not be null as its populated on run time behavior. It’s not possible to track the old data values from October to December or January based on this periodic dynamic changing the data. So separate alert cannot be set on this. There are already payment failure alerts in the system that runs on standard cases and based on them we can check whether the problem is at specific server and related to specific type of payment and specific country. So while there is this kind of problem so the possibility is to check the flow and look into the parameters that getting the null data and recache them again. E.g. payemtns, As per above form the parameters value depends on form of payments and then its sub elements like card issuing country, type of card OR in case paypel , transfer, installments payments. This behavior is as per existing application design. The stats from 21 to now are almost in equal range.. More detail can be found in attached email. [2018/02/22] LEDA.lnavio: reasignamos la incidencia para aclarar dudas.: Qué significa/implica “We have rebuilt this param today” (IBP_TARJETA_CREDITO_EXTERNAL_KEY) Qué impacto/mejora tiene ese “rebuilt”? El “problema” como se puede ver en las gráficas adjuntas (gráficas individuales por horas de cada día 18/19/20/21/22FEB) se solventó ese mismo día 19. El día 31JAN parece que lo que fallara fue en la pata A ¿fue el mismo motivo, IBP_TARJETA_CREDITO_EXTERNAL_KEY=null? El 8JAN parece que lo que fallara fue en la pata B ¿fue el mismo motivo, IBP_TARJETA_CREDITO_EXTERNAL_KEY=null? Si analizamos por patas y días las órdenes de compra en .mobi desde el 1NOV, se ve la caída en cada una de las ocasiones descritas ¿es siempre el mismo parámetro el que falla? ¿Por qué falla? Si ya sabemos que falla ¿no se puede poner una alerta? ¿hay algún plan para evitar esto y darnos cuenta siempre al día siguiente? Adjunto Excel de extracto totales por día de cada medición 01NOV-31DEC-2017 y 01JAN-22FEB*-2018 [2018/02/22]NIIT.vkumar:As per our observations we found that IBP_TARJETA_CREDITO_EXTERNAL_KEY was holding null data for some of the scenarios at pataB. We have rebuilt this param today. The payment confirmation trend seems fine now at both the pata’s as per attached detail. Advised user to valide the payment confirmation trend.

Resolution Description: 2/23/2018 8:04:37 PM, NIIT.averma, Hi Israel, This is not the error as it is as per design that Robots takes pause as per the time specified for them. In case of the EUR_EMD5 the pause is for 1 hour so it took the pause for that period after finishing the queue, that’s why the PNR was processed once Robot resumed its processing. Thanks and Regards, Anurag Verma 2/22/2018 7:49:09 PM, NIIT.averma, Since we have not seen this issue before, we have asked Israel for some more examples where we can analyse the pattern. Also there were no errors in the logs seen and robots were also up at that time though there were no processing done by them hence there was no logging in the logs. 2/22/2018 11:43:53 AM, NIIT.averma, I have checked these cases and found that some of the Robots has stopped processing on 14th Feb and resumed their process again on 15th Feb, though there was no error found in the logs and alert or error reported for Robot during that period. The reason for the gap in the processing is not clear as there is no traces. The PNRs provided by you are picked up by these robots on 15th Feb. That’s why the ticket was not processed for a long time when sent to the Robot BATCH. -rw-r--r-- 1 ibrobot ibcomgr 328642 Feb 14 13:41 eur_et1.log.2018-02-14 ibrobot@ibcrobotl:/delivery/robot-batch/ibrobot/logs> vi eur_et1.log.2018-02-15 #16:03:28,699#INFO #eur_et1 - Creando proceso: com.iberia.robot.emision.EmisionETProcess ...

We are therefore linking PBI000000052257 with this ticket. 02.27: [OPTIMA]: Mail received from suppliers that they have captured the relevant logs and are currently working on this case with priority and keep us posted on the updates shortly. 02.27-[OPTIMA]- We have asked the suppliers to give an ETA. 02.27-[OPTIMA]- the suppliers advised to get the xml request/response from the user. Incident Description: AGP - T-3 Pl 3 Oficina Personal * C280/A0ED022021691 - Mala calidad
Problemas con IBLEARNING-ELEARNING
Open incidence - Error in the IB-WEEKLY-MFLS-20180211090005.dat file
Resolution Description: Issue:-BI team has received the value of KMS 0 in IB-WEEKLY-MFLS-20180211090005.dat file. Impact:- BI Team was unable to load this file into database of British Airways. Analysis:-We did back tracking and investigate, there is PLSQL procedure CARGA_CIUDADES_DISTANCIA which has not run before generating this file and master tables was not updated. Resolution:-We Rerun the CARGA_CIUDADES_DISTANCIA procedure with the date of Sunday after the completion of this procedure,regenerate the file and send it to the BI team. Problem ticket required: No, The problem is known, CARGA_CIUDADES_DISTANCIA procedure should be schedule in the same script and should be execute before generating the file. Can this issue is prevented: Yes, Normal change is required to prevent this issue in future.

[K3AYFW /K3AYFW] Cash&Avios no emitido: ERROR TTP: IB RJT: **/NO EXISTE AUTORIZACION
Resolution Description: 2/21/18 5:41:16 PM, NIIT.RGAUTAM, Hi Israel, TKT has passed back the incident and replied with following comments. Please review and suggest next step. “Located. First I explain. Cash & Avios authorizations are made from IB.com and / or from .NET. So that, whoever does it, the TKT can be issued later, ATOS informs us through a message of the creation of the authorization. We (RES) register the F5 authorization and you (TKT) call us to validate it. But, for a long time, we have enough errors (XTCAs) in the processing of these messages. These errors occur because in the message, in the field dedicated to the CASH part, comes a number with negatives. Incident Description: No se permite recuperar PIN con pregunta secreta
Resolution Description: 2/27/2018 9:32:20 PM, NIIT.SKUMAR6, WE asked Luis for the same and waiting for his response. Sent email is attached. 2/26/2018 5:53:00 PM, NIIT.SKUMAR6, Got another response from Angel. He suggested us to get java decompiler and try to get java source code by decompiling it. we are trying to get it from our local DLA if possible. 2/25/2018 7:10:41 PM, NIIT.SKUMAR6, Angel has responded but we need source code of jar file is required. We have requested to know source code location of jar(iberiaSecurityKey-1.0.jar) for further investigation. 2/23/2018 8:53:36 PM, NIIT.SKUMAR6, Sent email to Angel for help. We have checked on code level and found that to decrypt secret answer there is one library method com.indra.iberia.util.security.SecurityManager.decrypt16CharsString() throwing exception even required information is in Database too. Email is attached. 2/21/2018 4:00:31 PM, NIIT.SKUMAR6, query that fetch ibplus user's record is: SELECT * FROM BV_USER, BV_USER_PROFILE, BV_IB_PROFILE, BV_IB_UNAUTHORIZED_ACCESS,BV_TR_PROFILE WHERE USER_STATE=0 AND BV_USER.USER_ID = BV_USER_PROFILE.USER_ID AND BV_USER.USER_ID = BV_IB_PROFILE.USER_ID AND BV_USER.USER_ID = BV_IB_UNAUTHORIZED_ACCESS.USER_ID AND BV_USER.USER_ID = BV_TR_PROFILE.USER_ID AND USER_ALIAS= '28483642' But still it's not matching with form data. 2/16/2018 10:01:49 PM, NIIT.SKUMAR6, We have moved one step ahead and found issue with com.indra.iberia.util.security.SecurityManager.decrypt16CharsString(getStringProperty(_SECRET_ANSWER)) and causing exception(BvVisitorException). 2/15/2018 10:55:29 PM, NIIT.SKUMAR6, Investigated further and found that the Bean IberiaVisitor(es.indra.iberia.visitor.IberiaVisitor.java) having method getSecretAnswer() which is responsible for getting correct answer from database but its returning null inplace for anser each time. Now we will check the query of this method fire to get the cause of showing exception. 2/5/2018 8:53:38 PM, NIIT.SKUMAR6, We have investigated on code level and found exception.Added details in workinfo. 2/1/2018 10:09:04 PM, NIIT.SKUMAR6, While investigating, Seems user first last name and secret question's answer is not going through the form data thats why it is showing one exception. Investigation going on, once get some concrete will update. 1/25/2018 4:31:44 PM, NIIT.SKUMAR6, Looking into this. 2018/01/23] LEDA.mclemente: Lo hemos probado con distintos usuarios de prueba. 1/22/2018 8:25:56 PM, NIIT.averma, We have asked digital support to suggest if this is happening for other users as well or this is specific to the only user mentioned in the incident ? We have looked into this and before we check this from code angle we need this information.

Queue 22 - OnHoldLogger - Localizador: , Error en la emision (TTM)
Resolution Description: I have checked the provided examples and there are traces in the portal logs where I have found that there was a FATAL error during online ancillaries emission. After that it was moved to queue 22 for further processing. The onhold request was confirmed on 15th JA for UBCE94 and 14th JAN for UBLRYS. The issue occurred during TTM command. “ FATAL - [ OnHoldAction::securePerform::onHoldEMDIssue ] >> HBFF. Se hizo la autorizacion DE 476486 pero no se ha completado la operacion de onHoldEMDIssue del PNR UBCE94 java.rmi.RemoteException::OnHoldService; nested exception is: [423]-Enqueued to MADIB0009/22C4. Cause: Error TTM: java.rmi.RemoteException: OnHoldService; nested exception is: [423]-Enqueued to MADIB0009/22C4. Cause: Error TTM: ” Though there is no information found for these two PNRs in the Robot logs. UBCE94 12/01/2018 UBLRYS 12/01/2018 Could you please suggest if this error is still occurring, if yes please provide some more recent examples to analyze further.

Resolution Description: [2018/02/13] LEDA.lnavio:adjuntamos fichero semanal con 1.816 transacciones con AMEX en países y monedas donde 3DS está disponible, 1.724 casos con el campo a NO y 89 a SI (3 en blanco, lo cual también es incorrecto) [2018/01/30] LEDA.agarciab: Adjuntamos información solicitada 1/30/2018 5:36:25 PM, NIIT.averma, I have checked the two PNR examples and checked logs to find the what is actually the issue here. Also I have some queries as well regarding the configurations that what should be actual behavior in ideal case. PNR: QHV39Z In this case the 3DS available was sent as YES, which we have seen in our logs as well. PNR: POZ6HJ In this case the user has tried four times and each time the card was rejected. First three time user has used the VISA CREDIT,BANK OF AMERICA - CONSUMER CREDIT and each time the 3DS available was sent as YES and fourth time user has used AMERICAN EXPRESS CREDIT,AMERICAN EXPRESS US CONSUMER and this time it was sent as NO. Since both these cases are the wrong ones, we have asked digital business on the below queries as it will help to find out the cause faster: - What are the ideal working scenarios ? - What was reflected in CYB in the first three transactions of PNR POZ6HJ ? - What should be the actual configurations ? In parallel we are also investigating. Attached is the email sent to digital support team. 1/22/18 5:17:06 PM, NIIT.RGAUTAM, We have investigated and didn’t found any relevant data regarding the PNR UDTV69 provided as example in the incident. We cannot see the FP and other details. Since this PNR is showing cancelled BY START OVER in the Amadeus logs . Please provide more examples so we can understand the flow better and proceed to our investigation. Mail Attached.

Queue 22 - Error TTP: CT RJT: UNABLE TO PROCESS
Resolution Description: [2018-02-16]NIIT.vsharma It has been checked with Resiber team and they suspect issue to be at Amadeus side. An IR (14722128) has been raised with Amadeus to look into it further. Please refer to attached email for further details. Marking the incident Pending/Third Party Action Required. [2018-02-14]NIIT.vsharma Resiber team we seek your help to understand the scenario when the error mentioned in this incident is seen. FYI- We have done the initial investigation of the issue and so far, it does not seem to be due to code. The error message comes in the response of TTP command execution and is handled under emission exception at the code level and going by the names of different available exceptions handled in the code, it seems to be something gone wrong at the Amadeus or RESIBER side after firing the TTP command. Passing the incident to your queue. For further details please see attached email for details of investigation. 30/01/18 - Increase of errors, see notes.
